Pacific Lighting Corp said it isconsidering the sale of its land development line of businessand will be initiating discussions with potential buyers.    The book value of the company's investment in landdevelopment operations is 224 mln dlrs. The Pacific LightingReal Estate Group earned 24.2 mln dlrs and employed 800 peopleduring 1986, the company said.    Alternatives to the sale being considered include a masterlimited partnership and an initial public offering of theequity in the land development companies, it said.    Proceeds from the sale would likely be invested in PacificLightings' new specialty retailing line of business and its oiland gas operations, the company said.    The investment banking firm Morgan Stanley has beenretained to advise Pacific Lighting on the disposition of theland development operations.    Completion of a transaction, it one is made, is expected bythe end of the year, the company said. Reuter&#3;